1
00:00:05,713 --> 00:00:08,870
Dr. Bonten, thank you for today.

2
00:00:09,330 --> 00:00:10,890
Thank you.

3
00:00:13,976 --> 00:00:14,976
Shall we begin?

4
00:00:15,005 --> 00:00:16,113
Yes, Doctor.

5
00:00:16,153 --> 00:00:17,499
You. Do it!

6
00:00:17,539 --> 00:00:18,746
Yes.

7
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:28,280
We'll now begin coronary artery bypass
for unstable angina.

8
00:00:28,684 --> 00:00:29,966
- Scalpel.
- Here.

9
00:00:32,540 --> 00:00:33,933
- Bovie.
- Here.

10
00:00:40,403 --> 00:00:42,023
- Retractor.
- Here.

11
00:00:45,626 --> 00:00:46,966
- Mayo scissors.
- Here.

12
00:00:49,413 --> 00:00:51,373
- Start bypass.
- Got it.

13
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:56,999
Lower it.

14
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:02,620
This song is
apparently Dr. Bonten's theme music.

15
00:01:03,113 --> 00:01:05,853
His surgery is truly majestic.

16
00:01:06,140 --> 00:01:08,280
Indeed, Director. Most impressive.

17
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:14,913
I never imagined I'd witness a surgery
on a former prime minister with my own eyes.

18
00:01:15,860 --> 00:01:19,153
Now that we have
one of Japan's top cardiac surgeons,

19
00:01:19,193 --> 00:01:23,533
the new hospital project is
finally becoming a reality.

20
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:28,080
Best of God Hand?

21
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:30,639
He's Japan's top cardiac surgeon.

22
00:01:30,679 --> 00:01:31,879
Huh.

23
00:01:31,926 --> 00:01:35,326
Why would someone like that transfer
from Touou University Hospital to us?

24
00:01:36,144 --> 00:01:37,437
Who knows.

25
00:01:37,606 --> 00:01:39,484
The director recruited him, apparently.

26
00:01:39,524 --> 00:01:40,524
Recruited?

27
00:01:40,552 --> 00:01:44,960
They're gathering top doctors
from across the country for the new hospital.

28
00:01:45,037 --> 00:01:47,237
So the new hospital really is happening.

29
00:01:47,596 --> 00:01:50,660
I came back to make
the new hospital a reality.

30
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:55,320
To that end, the unprofitable ER will be
shut down soon.

31
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:59,300
So Dr. Tamon betrayed
the emergency department.

32
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:04,700
While Dr. Tamon was away,
you kept fighting all alone.

33
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:08,800
A kid who can't even treat patients alone has
no business worrying about me!

34
00:02:11,696 --> 00:02:18,336
Former Prime Minister Tagawa's
coronary bypass surgery was a success.

35
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:26,120
Dr. Bonten, your thoughts
after completing the surgery?

36
00:02:26,860 --> 00:02:32,300
It'd be a lie to say there was no pressure,
but I was confident I'd succeed.

37
00:02:33,380 --> 00:02:40,480
Because my surgeries have
a 99 percent success rate.

38
00:02:42,576 --> 00:02:47,280
Dr. Bonten, why did you transfer
from Touou University Hospital to Taishaku?

39
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:52,660
Well, I share the chairwoman's vision.
But the biggest reason was

40
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:58,480
that I heard Dr. Tamon had returned
as vice director.

41
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:06,820
I had no idea you were
classmates in university.

42
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:10,000
Dr. Tamon was always number one
at our university,

43
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:13,156
and I could never match him.

44
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,660
Now he's completely surpassed me, though.

45
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:22,580
I'm truly grateful for the opportunity
to work with a close friend.

46
00:03:23,179 --> 00:03:26,540
To ensure you can shine
at the new hospital,

47
00:03:26,793 --> 00:03:30,340
we absolutely must make
the inspection in two days a success.

48
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,012
Inspection?

49
00:03:32,052 --> 00:03:33,278
Yes.

50
00:03:34,726 --> 00:03:38,866
We're hosting Steve Fink, CEO of Gold Wealth.

51
00:03:38,906 --> 00:03:41,660
Wait, you mean
that
Fink?

52
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:45,420
It's through Dr. Tamon's connections
from his time overseas.

53
00:03:46,486 --> 00:03:50,680
I can't believe the CEO of a world-leading
financial company is coming here.

54
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:55,540
It's a precious chance to secure funding
for the new hospital.

55
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,620
Dr. Tamon, we're counting on you.

56
00:03:59,009 --> 00:04:00,296
Leave it to me.

57
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,660
Hey! That's Dr. Daikoku's!

58
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:12,420
If it's in the fridge, it's fair game.

59
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:37,226
Do you think Dr. Tamon will
really shut down the ER?

60
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:44,780
I know it's not my place to butt in,
but I can't help worrying.

61
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,700
Don't worry.
I'll never let them shut it down.

62
00:04:49,823 --> 00:04:51,023
But...

63
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:56,708
Incoming.

64
00:04:57,276 --> 00:04:58,476
Huh?

65
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:00,582
Mitsuko Namino, age 70.

66
00:05:00,622 --> 00:05:05,170
She collapsed on the street unconscious,
but was alert when paramedics arrived.

67
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:08,350
Cardiac arrest for more than three seconds,
possibly sick sinus syndrome.

68
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:12,470
That's when the sinus node is damaged
and the heart rate drops, right?

69
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:16,110
Without a pacemaker to maintain heart rate,
another episode could be fatal.

70
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:18,430
We need to consult cardiology
or cardiac surgery.

71
00:05:18,470 --> 00:05:20,990
I contacted them,
but they said they're too busy.

72
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:24,050
Then I'll place a temporary pacemaker.

73
00:05:24,516 --> 00:05:27,110
Wait, you can do that?

74
00:05:27,150 --> 00:05:28,396
Prep the cath lab.

75
00:05:29,128 --> 00:05:30,422
Wow.

76
00:05:33,210 --> 00:05:36,210
Today's surgery was truly magnificent.

77
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:40,716
Honestly, being in the spotlight isn't
really my forte.

78
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:42,850
Oh, don't be so modest.

79
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:47,130
You'll be the one leading
this hospital someday.

80
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:53,690
The only one who could succeed me
as hospital director is you, Dr. Bonten.

81
00:05:54,136 --> 00:05:56,123
I'd be honored.

82
00:05:57,110 --> 00:06:01,443
To that end, let's start by securing
the vice director position for you.

83
00:06:02,130 --> 00:06:03,510
By dragging Tamon down...

84
00:06:06,683 --> 00:06:07,923
Yes.

85
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,970
That's exactly my intention.

86
00:06:41,085 --> 00:06:44,899
Dr. Ashura

87
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:51,140
Despite all my warnings, it seems
you've broken the rules again.

88
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:56,560
Effective today, you're relieved
as Head of the Emergency Department.

89
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:03,340
What a waste.

90
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:06,280
It is regrettable.

91
00:07:08,486 --> 00:07:12,580
But my son's life was saved,
so I have no regrets.

92
00:07:13,461 --> 00:07:16,166
- What?
- I'll work hard as staff.

93
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,860
Excuse me.

94
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:26,116
Well... I really did it now.

95
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:30,710
Let's grab something sweet
and push through this.

96
00:07:32,423 --> 00:07:34,150
Hey, make way for me.

97
00:07:34,263 --> 00:07:36,463
Dr. Bonten, we look forward
to working with you.

98
00:07:36,963 --> 00:07:38,336
Good to have you with us.

99
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:41,630
Everyone, please, let's not do this.

100
00:07:42,063 --> 00:07:44,090
We're all colleagues here.

101
00:07:44,576 --> 00:07:47,616
Let's aim for the world stage together.

102
00:07:47,656 --> 00:07:49,230
Yes, sir. All right, let's go.

103
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:52,730
This is inefficient. Let's drop
this entourage parade, too.

104
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:54,150
Oh, but Dr. Bonten...

105
00:08:00,106 --> 00:08:01,746
The temporary pacemaker patient?

106
00:08:02,066 --> 00:08:05,265
Oh, Ms. Namino was taken
by cardiac surgery earlier.

107
00:08:05,305 --> 00:08:07,720
I heard they're implanting
a permanent pacemaker.

108
00:08:08,486 --> 00:08:10,086
What brought that on?

109
00:08:10,305 --> 00:08:14,960
With Dr. Bonten here, they want full beds
to make their department look good.

110
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,120
Then maybe they'll take over
our patients more quickly now.

111
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:21,280
Lucky patient, getting treated
by the God Hand.

112
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,640
I'll go check it out.

113
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:30,120
So even she is curious about Dr. Bonten.

114
00:08:31,170 --> 00:08:32,173
I'm going, too.

115
00:08:32,213 --> 00:08:33,820
Huh? How come?

116
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,840
We can't have her causing a scene in Surgery.

117
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,840
We already handed off the patient.
Don't go stirring up trouble.

118
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:51,116
Look, she's sleeping.
Let's not wake her. Let's go.

119
00:08:51,243 --> 00:08:52,523
- No.
- Huh?

120
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:54,650
Wake up. Wake up.

121
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:56,870
Could her consciousness level be dropping?

122
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:58,850
Hey, wake up. Wake up!

123
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:00,016
The temporary's come out.

124
00:09:00,056 --> 00:09:01,263
Wake up!

125
00:09:01,470 --> 00:09:04,490
Next is a patient with sick sinus syndrome.

126
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:09,090
The ER doctor placed a temporary pacer.
Proper implantation is scheduled for today.

127
00:09:09,116 --> 00:09:11,216
The ER doctor placed a temporary pacer?

128
00:09:11,516 --> 00:09:15,077
So your cardiologists here also work
in emergency medicine?

129
00:09:15,117 --> 00:09:17,390
No, um, Ashura is
an emergency medicine specialist.

130
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:19,570
Ashura?

131
00:09:19,710 --> 00:09:23,890
Her real name is Anno.
But she's like a literal Ashura.

132
00:09:24,446 --> 00:09:25,450
Hurry!

133
00:09:25,490 --> 00:09:26,963
Dr. Daikoku!

134
00:09:27,056 --> 00:09:28,623
Ashura, what are you doing?!

135
00:09:28,979 --> 00:09:31,650
- The temporary electrode came off the heart.
- What?

136
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:35,410
Another cardiac arrest without treatment,
and she dies. I'm implanting the pacemaker.

137
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,050
Hey, wait! Don't just do whatever you want!

138
00:09:38,090 --> 00:09:40,950
- Move.
- Wait! That patient belongs to Surgery now!

139
00:09:41,123 --> 00:09:43,970
- Out of my way!
- Do you even know what you're doing?!

140
00:09:44,010 --> 00:09:45,870
Anno, that's enough! Leave it to them!

141
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:46,922
Get out of my way!

142
00:09:46,962 --> 00:09:48,716
Let go!

143
00:09:50,883 --> 00:09:53,603
Dr. Kongo, please calm down.

144
00:09:54,169 --> 00:09:55,409
But...

145
00:09:55,570 --> 00:10:01,290
Dr. Anno's anger is justified.
This oversight is our responsibility.

146
00:10:07,716 --> 00:10:10,183
I sincerely apologize.

147
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:14,523
The God Hand just...

148
00:10:17,336 --> 00:10:19,636
He bows his head pretty easily.

149
00:10:19,989 --> 00:10:21,215
So, who are you?

150
00:10:24,672 --> 00:10:25,672
Oh, it's over.

151
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:28,171
Hey! Do you know who this man is?!
Apologize now!

152
00:10:28,211 --> 00:10:29,785
The patient's on death's door.

153
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,940
I can't leave this to you. We're taking over.

154
00:10:34,655 --> 00:10:35,960
Hey, stop it.

155
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,432
It's fine, Dr. Kongo.

156
00:10:38,472 --> 00:10:43,420
She cared enough to come all the way here
from emergency medicine to check.

157
00:10:47,463 --> 00:10:48,903
Is the pacemaker working?

158
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,410
Yeah, it's good.

159
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:51,683
Okay, closing up.

160
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,790
Anno caused another scene, I take it.

161
00:10:54,137 --> 00:10:58,737
Stealing a patient from Surgery...
Quite the caring doctor.

162
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,850
That woman is apparently Tamon's protégé.

163
00:11:02,890 --> 00:11:04,116
Dr. Tamon's?

164
00:11:04,436 --> 00:11:05,696
Yes.

165
00:11:06,030 --> 00:11:07,830
What an infuriating pair.

166
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:10,310
I must be grateful for meeting Ashura.

167
00:11:10,742 --> 00:11:11,988
What do you mean?

168
00:11:13,576 --> 00:11:18,071
Thanks to her,
I've come up with a wonderful plan.

169
00:11:18,723 --> 00:11:23,510
The success rate is... 99 percent.

170
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:36,420
Thank you all for taking the time
to gather here today.

171
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:43,240
I'm Bonten, newly appointed
to Taishaku General Hospital.

172
00:11:56,830 --> 00:12:01,830
Dr. Bonten!
These are letters addressed to you.

173
00:12:02,996 --> 00:12:04,310
Thank you.

174
00:12:05,110 --> 00:12:09,750
What an incredible number!
All these patients are waiting for you.

175
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:13,596
I wish I could operate on every one of them.

176
00:12:13,636 --> 00:12:19,356
Your schedule is tacked... I mean,
packed for a year in advance, right?

177
00:12:19,450 --> 00:12:22,950
It pains me that I can't help everyone.

178
00:12:23,303 --> 00:12:24,550
So cool.

179
00:12:25,836 --> 00:12:29,936
Just when my husband and I were
about to give up hope,

180
00:12:30,090 --> 00:12:32,650
we learned about Dr. Bonten on TV.

181
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:39,490
You are our last hope. Please, Doctor,
use your skills to save my husband.

182
00:12:40,523 --> 00:12:45,110
Over 62, huh....
If only he were two years younger.

183
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:50,756
Over 60 is high-risk. Too bad.

184
00:12:53,123 --> 00:12:59,750
This one has a high risk
of postoperative complications. No way.

185
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:04,256
This one's no good either.

186
00:13:05,819 --> 00:13:09,050
Almost good. But no.

187
00:13:10,243 --> 00:13:11,956
No...

188
00:13:16,316 --> 00:13:20,870
Age 50 with this condition.
No prior medical history.

189
00:13:22,283 --> 00:13:23,502
Accepted.

190
00:13:25,650 --> 00:13:30,811
Oh my, only one letter left.

191
00:13:35,656 --> 00:13:37,189
It can't be helped.

192
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:42,535
To maintain my 99 percent success rate,

193
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:47,300
I have no choice
but to turn away high-risk patients.

194
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:24,390
Hematemesis patient. BP 100 over 58.
Oxygen saturation is 98.

195
00:14:25,785 --> 00:14:27,396
Hello, Taishaku Emergency Department.

196
00:14:27,436 --> 00:14:30,090
Female in her 20s, acute abdomen.
Requesting admission.

197
00:14:30,130 --> 00:14:32,370
Understood. We can take her.

198
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,049
Another patient is incoming.

199
00:14:35,089 --> 00:14:38,350
Another? Aren't there way too many
of them today?

200
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:40,430
Ten patients in one hour?
What's going on?

201
00:14:40,470 --> 00:14:42,850
- Start oxygen and two IV lines.
- Yes, Doctor.

202
00:14:43,057 --> 00:14:44,283
Opening your mouth now.

203
00:14:44,983 --> 00:14:46,203
Intubating.

204
00:14:48,356 --> 00:14:51,323
- Cross-clamping. Flow down.
- Understood.

205
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:55,143
- Backup. Pressure start.
- Understood.

206
00:14:57,363 --> 00:14:58,943
How long has it been?

207
00:14:58,955 --> 00:15:00,209
It's 45 minutes now.

208
00:15:00,349 --> 00:15:01,569
Right on track.

209
00:15:01,790 --> 00:15:04,650
My surgeries always run on schedule.

210
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:12,095
Doctor, bleeding is increasing.

211
00:15:12,135 --> 00:15:13,428
Hold on a moment.

212
00:15:15,343 --> 00:15:16,422
- Sorry.
- I got it.

213
00:15:16,462 --> 00:15:18,822
- Take him to CT. Contact the Operating Room.
- Got it.

214
00:15:18,862 --> 00:15:20,362
- Coming through!
- Oh, sorry.

215
00:15:20,648 --> 00:15:22,750
We're way understaffed. This is bad.

216
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:27,483
The hematemesis patient's BP is
unreadable. Orders, please.

217
00:15:27,523 --> 00:15:28,523
What?

218
00:15:28,550 --> 00:15:31,470
- Add a line! Four units of RBCs.
- Understood!

219
00:15:32,589 --> 00:15:34,483
So many at once...

220
00:15:35,822 --> 00:15:37,116
We can't handle any more.

221
00:15:39,782 --> 00:15:41,176
Kid, tell them we accept.

222
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:44,016
But we're already treating so many!

223
00:15:44,056 --> 00:15:45,309
It's fine. Do it.

224
00:15:48,162 --> 00:15:49,162
Yes.

225
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:51,042
Male, 65-year-old, collapsed at home.

226
00:15:51,082 --> 00:15:54,677
GCS is 2-10, dyspnea present.
Possible heart failure.

227
00:15:55,523 --> 00:15:56,803
Please admit this patient.

228
00:15:57,710 --> 00:15:59,650
Stop spacing out. Admit them now.

229
00:16:04,963 --> 00:16:07,263
What happened? Are you okay?

230
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:14,450
Sorry, we're full of patients right now.

231
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,510
We can't admit any more.

232
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,200
We'll take them. Bring them now.

233
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:28,660
Doctor, we really can't handle more.

234
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:31,740
Since another one is coming,
move stable patients to the ICU.

235
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,040
The ICU is already full.

236
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,780
Then find any ward with a bed.

237
00:16:34,959 --> 00:16:36,200
I'll contact the wards.

238
00:16:37,993 --> 00:16:39,569
Enough is enough!

239
00:16:39,609 --> 00:16:43,729
The patients here are already in
a critical state. They all need treatment!

240
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:46,126
There's no way we can handle
any more than this.

241
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:50,659
- Doctor, the wards can't take anyone yet.
- Then we treat them in the hall. Set it up.

242
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,133
- Understood.
- The hallway?

243
00:16:56,213 --> 00:16:57,413
Asystole!

244
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:58,793
Administer adrenaline.

245
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:07,573
This isn't medical care...

246
00:17:08,060 --> 00:17:09,890
- Give another dose.
- Yes.

247
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:14,080
Doctor, this is like an assembly line
in a factory!

248
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:16,680
We took them in, so we treat them.
If you won't help, get out.

249
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,693
Just send them to another hospital!

250
00:17:18,733 --> 00:17:20,160
If we make a mistake...

251
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,100
Adrenaline ready. I'll take over.

252
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,680
The patients wouldn't want this either!

253
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,153
This is nothing but arrogance!

254
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,920
I almost died once.

255
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:39,170
So I can never abandon a patient
who's calling for help. Never.

256
00:17:43,123 --> 00:17:44,430
- Stop.
- Understood.

257
00:17:53,060 --> 00:17:54,303
Heartbeat's back.

258
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:57,716
- Doctor, the ambulance has arrived.
- Got it.

259
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:07,550
Dr. Yakushiji, what should we do?

260
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:12,470
Move stable patients out to the hallway.

261
00:18:13,756 --> 00:18:15,689
Your stay in Japan will be
short this time...

262
00:18:15,729 --> 00:18:17,210
Excuse me, coming through.

263
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:19,170
Dr. Daikoku, what on earth happened?

264
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:22,730
The ER is overwhelmed with critical patients.

265
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,616
That's terrible.

266
00:18:24,862 --> 00:18:26,616
- Excuse me.
- Right.

267
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:31,143
There's no problem at all.

268
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:39,463
Shall we move on
to the finishing touches?

269
00:18:39,503 --> 00:18:40,722
Understood.

270
00:18:42,510 --> 00:18:43,789
- Forceps.
- Here.

271
00:18:43,829 --> 00:18:45,369
- Prolene suture 4-0.
- Here.

272
00:18:51,870 --> 00:18:57,770
We have excellent staff
and never refuse a patient.

273
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:04,290
We'd be honored to be your first choice
when deciding where to transport patients.

274
00:19:08,813 --> 00:19:09,813
Locked.

275
00:19:09,841 --> 00:19:11,800
- On three...
- One, two, three.

276
00:19:12,363 --> 00:19:14,486
- Respiratory failure in transit.
- Kid, intubate.

277
00:19:14,526 --> 00:19:15,926
I'm in the middle of a CV.

278
00:19:16,327 --> 00:19:18,127
I can't, I'm still in surgery.

279
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:19,370
- Max out the oxygen.
- Got it.

280
00:19:19,410 --> 00:19:20,840
- Start an IV line.
- Got it.

281
00:19:21,284 --> 00:19:23,738
Doctor, this patient is
having status asthmaticus.

282
00:19:23,778 --> 00:19:25,191
- Subcutaneous adrenaline.
- Got it.

283
00:19:25,231 --> 00:19:26,973
The patient in the hallway just vomited.

284
00:19:27,013 --> 00:19:29,251
- I'll be right there. Get an IV line in.
- Got it.

285
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:32,844
Doctor, we have V-fib.

286
00:19:37,253 --> 00:19:39,460
He says the architecture is wonderful.

287
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,420
It reminds him of his hometown, Brooklyn.

288
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:42,946
Thank you.

289
00:19:42,986 --> 00:19:45,460
- Prep the defibrillator. Charge to 150.
- Got it.

290
00:19:53,896 --> 00:19:55,323
Please, have a seat.

291
00:20:08,013 --> 00:20:09,446
- Clear!
- Understood.

292
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:12,894
- Heartbeat not restored.
- Again.

293
00:20:12,934 --> 00:20:15,473
The patient in the hallway has deteriorated.
Respiratory arrest.

294
00:20:15,513 --> 00:20:17,700
- Bag the patient. I'll be right there.
- Got it.

295
00:20:18,006 --> 00:20:19,006
What did she say?

296
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:21,473
- She can't come yet. Prep the Ambu bag.
- Got it.

297
00:20:22,606 --> 00:20:23,952
- It's here.
- Got it.

298
00:20:24,226 --> 00:20:25,446
Charging done.

299
00:20:27,306 --> 00:20:28,565
- Clear!
- Understood.

300
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:32,100
No good. No heartbeat.

301
00:20:36,973 --> 00:20:38,853
That's it, then.

302
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:40,613
Good work.

303
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:48,273
Are you okay? Let me take a look.

304
00:20:51,519 --> 00:20:52,792
Charging done.

305
00:20:54,499 --> 00:20:55,726
- Clear!
- Yes.

306
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,060
Come back to us.

307
00:21:09,970 --> 00:21:11,330
Heartbeat's back.

308
00:21:12,649 --> 00:21:14,809
Kid, take over. I'll check
on the hallway patient.

309
00:21:27,517 --> 00:21:29,297
The hallway patient is stable.

310
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:46,480
Focus on that patient. I'll handle the rest.

311
00:21:48,509 --> 00:21:49,713
Got it.

312
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:54,339
Resident, place an arterial line
on the heart failure patient.

313
00:21:54,379 --> 00:21:56,506
- I'll handle the trauma hemorrhage.
- Yes, sir.

314
00:21:58,032 --> 00:21:59,318
More incoming.

315
00:22:05,643 --> 00:22:10,303
Accept every single one.
We will save every patient.

316
00:22:10,449 --> 00:22:11,722
Understood!

317
00:22:22,660 --> 00:22:28,700
He can't help himself around patients.
I suppose that's an ER doctor for you.

318
00:22:35,391 --> 00:22:38,585
Oh, please wait, Mr. Fink!

319
00:22:38,625 --> 00:22:41,105
Please, just a moment longer.

320
00:22:44,610 --> 00:22:46,303
It seems he's finally back.

321
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:52,696
Dr. Bonten, weren't you doing surgery?

322
00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:56,330
My surgeries always finish right on schedule.

323
00:22:58,237 --> 00:23:00,776
Is Dr. Tamon not here?

324
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:03,950
He should be here soon.

325
00:23:03,990 --> 00:23:06,780
Then allow me to give
the presentation in his place.

326
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:18,619
- Two more patients are arriving shortly.
- Got it!

327
00:23:18,659 --> 00:23:21,339
- Ichikawa, watch the respiratory management.
- Got it.

328
00:23:21,426 --> 00:23:23,279
Stop Murata's bleeding,
then transfer to ortho.

329
00:23:23,319 --> 00:23:24,319
Yes.

330
00:23:24,346 --> 00:23:27,631
Prep CT for Takato. Get a line in
and prep the ultrasound for Yoshida.

331
00:23:27,671 --> 00:23:28,873
Got it!

332
00:23:32,086 --> 00:23:37,800
It's so calm in here,
even with all these patients.

333
00:23:38,929 --> 00:23:40,129
So calm.

334
00:23:41,416 --> 00:23:44,720
Sayama's bleeding is severe.
Might need emergency surgery.

335
00:23:44,740 --> 00:23:47,100
I'll be done in 40 seconds.
I'll handle the bleeding.

336
00:23:47,460 --> 00:23:51,640
This calm atmosphere...
I guess it's because those two are here.

337
00:23:55,050 --> 00:23:58,190
Dr. Tamon, is this okay?
Didn't you have an important guest?

338
00:23:58,390 --> 00:24:01,990
Right now, let's just focus
on saving our patients.

339
00:24:02,268 --> 00:24:03,476
Got it.

340
00:24:16,490 --> 00:24:21,491
If you hadn't stepped in,
I don't know what we'd have done.

341
00:24:21,952 --> 00:24:22,970
I'm grateful.

342
00:24:23,010 --> 00:24:30,830
Not at all. If you'd like, shall I attend
tomorrow's dinner with Fink as well?

343
00:24:32,090 --> 00:24:33,770
Oh? What do you mean?

344
00:24:34,730 --> 00:24:38,403
My surgeries always finish right on schedule.

345
00:24:39,570 --> 00:24:44,996
Unlike a certain someone,
Dr. Bonten wouldn't embarrass you like this.

346
00:24:47,389 --> 00:24:52,178
Is that the real reason you came here?

347
00:24:53,889 --> 00:24:59,291
Ambitious, aren't you?
I don't mind that. I'll think about it.

348
00:25:00,110 --> 00:25:01,543
Thank you.

349
00:25:08,452 --> 00:25:11,897
- Things have finally calmed down.
- More patients might come in, though.

350
00:25:11,945 --> 00:25:14,470
- Get some rest while you can.
- Yes, sir.

351
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:18,440
I can't move anymore.

352
00:25:18,930 --> 00:25:22,100
Chiba? That's pretty far to come from.

353
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:25,300
It's faster than getting rejected
by multiple hospitals.

354
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:28,323
- Sure, come anytime.
- Thank you.

355
00:25:32,180 --> 00:25:35,500
- Dr. Bonten wasn't here after all.
- It's a shame.

356
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:38,380
I figured he'd be running the ER.

357
00:25:39,426 --> 00:25:42,402
Hold on. What do you mean by that?

358
00:25:45,476 --> 00:25:46,680
Come in.

359
00:25:49,576 --> 00:25:54,140
The chairwoman told me
you handled Fink on my behalf.

360
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:55,180
Thank you.

361
00:25:55,210 --> 00:25:59,260
It was nothing. I just did
what any friend would do.

362
00:25:59,540 --> 00:26:02,320
No, I really appreciate it. See you.

363
00:26:04,540 --> 00:26:07,580
Actually, there's something
I want to discuss.

364
00:26:09,582 --> 00:26:10,793
What is it?

365
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:17,100
When you heard the ER was in trouble,
you couldn't help but rush in to help.

366
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,780
No, I just had a responsibility
as clinical department chief.

367
00:26:23,493 --> 00:26:24,933
Is that really all?

368
00:26:27,180 --> 00:26:29,780
Didn't your emergency medicine
instincts kick in?

369
00:26:31,482 --> 00:26:33,300
I was just trying to avoid trouble...

370
00:26:33,340 --> 00:26:37,260
Deep down, don't you want to save lives
with your own hands?

371
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:46,250
The new hospital project...
Let me handle it for you.

372
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,916
Please. I want to help you.

373
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:59,700
I hear you went around bowing
to the paramedics, too.

374
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:04,563
The paramedics told me everything.

375
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:09,460
You tried to flood the ER
with patients to overwhelm it.

376
00:27:11,713 --> 00:27:14,576
What are you talking about?
Don't make wild accusations.

377
00:27:20,629 --> 00:27:21,829
Incoming.

378
00:27:28,335 --> 00:27:29,335
Yes?

379
00:27:29,362 --> 00:27:32,760
Dr. Tamon, Fink collapsed at his hotel.

380
00:27:33,799 --> 00:27:35,059
Fink?

381
00:27:36,093 --> 00:27:37,973
An ambulance is bringing him here now.

382
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:42,860
He's essential to us.
Save him no matter what.

383
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:49,203
Come with me to the battlefield.

384
00:28:08,843 --> 00:28:12,060
Huh? We weren't even called.

385
00:28:19,063 --> 00:28:20,090
What's going on?

386
00:28:20,130 --> 00:28:21,330
Bringing a patient.

387
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:23,303
Steve Fink?

388
00:28:23,530 --> 00:28:25,723
Just get an IV line in. Prep the ultrasound.

389
00:28:25,970 --> 00:28:27,190
Ah, got it.

390
00:28:34,656 --> 00:28:36,136
There's something in his heart.

391
00:28:37,548 --> 00:28:38,754
What is this?

392
00:28:39,195 --> 00:28:40,401
What do you think?

393
00:28:41,490 --> 00:28:43,630
- Let's get a contrast CT.
- Right away.

394
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:47,630
This is bad. This could get complicated.

395
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,840
A malignant cardiac tumor?

396
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:59,780
If the right ventricular outflow tract is
blocked, he dies. Critical condition.

397
00:29:00,340 --> 00:29:04,780
If I operate and save Fink,
the director's seat is as good as mine.

398
00:29:04,933 --> 00:29:05,933
However...

399
00:29:05,959 --> 00:29:10,948
Malignant cardiac tumor surgery is
high-risk and technically challenging.

400
00:29:11,170 --> 00:29:13,366
I don't want to be blamed if he dies.

401
00:29:13,692 --> 00:29:14,971
We operate now.

402
00:29:16,846 --> 00:29:22,690
Wait. Even if we surgically remove it,
the recurrence rate is high.

403
00:29:22,885 --> 00:29:26,466
We should consider other options
like carbon-ion radiotherapy.

404
00:29:26,580 --> 00:29:28,300
You can see there's no time for that.

405
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:34,580
I'm the cardiac specialist here.
Don't lecture me, ER doctor.

406
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:48,670
You just don't want to operate.

407
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:55,241
If he dies, it'll be a catastrophe.

408
00:29:55,859 --> 00:29:57,648
The hospital's reputation will plummet.

409
00:29:58,505 --> 00:30:01,224
The new hospital project will never happen.

410
00:30:01,264 --> 00:30:03,099
That’s unrelated to the patient.

411
00:30:05,491 --> 00:30:06,804
Dr. Bonten.

412
00:30:09,670 --> 00:30:11,903
Please, perform the surgery.

413
00:30:12,976 --> 00:30:15,471
You're a cardiac specialist.

414
00:30:15,990 --> 00:30:19,190
You're the only one who can save him.

415
00:30:26,986 --> 00:30:32,302
This is bad. Terrible.
It's a disaster. Damn it.

416
00:30:32,342 --> 00:30:35,940
I can't possibly say I can't do it
in front of Tamon.

417
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:42,108
I carefully selected only easy patients
to maintain my 99 percent success rate.

418
00:30:42,443 --> 00:30:45,880
That's why I've never done
a single high-risk operation.

419
00:30:46,086 --> 00:30:47,312
Dr. Bonten.

420
00:30:48,735 --> 00:30:51,222
You've been washing your hands
for over ten minutes now.

421
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:55,980
Sorry. I was mentally simulating the surgery.

422
00:30:56,447 --> 00:30:59,262
As expected of you. Please proceed then.

423
00:30:59,946 --> 00:31:03,959
Dr. Bonten. 99 percent.

424
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:08,647
I have to find a way to get out of this.

425
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:13,665
I know. I'll pretend
I'm feeling ill and call it off.

426
00:31:14,359 --> 00:31:16,045
The media's already at the hotel.

427
00:31:16,085 --> 00:31:17,879
Foreign press is there, too.

428
00:31:17,919 --> 00:31:21,121
The chairwoman is holding
a press conference after the surgery.

429
00:31:21,386 --> 00:31:24,292
- This is worldwide news.
- Amazing.

430
00:31:31,301 --> 00:31:34,177
Dr. Bonten. We're ready for you.

431
00:31:34,402 --> 00:31:36,209
We're in your hands.

432
00:31:36,709 --> 00:31:39,455
This is bad. This is bad.

433
00:31:39,495 --> 00:31:45,063
Bad, bad, bad, bad, bad,
bad, bad, bad, bad, bad...

434
00:31:45,296 --> 00:31:48,343
Bad, bad, bad, bad, bad, bad...

435
00:31:48,383 --> 00:31:50,242
Dr. Bonten, is everything all right?

436
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:55,596
Oh, right,
that
. Hey, you.

437
00:31:55,662 --> 00:31:56,955
Oh, sorry.

438
00:32:00,850 --> 00:32:03,863
Now then, once more,
we're in your hands, Doctor.

439
00:32:04,182 --> 00:32:05,863
We're in your hands.

440
00:32:06,289 --> 00:32:11,156
Bad, bad, bad, bad, bad,
bad, bad, bad, bad, bad...

441
00:32:12,129 --> 00:32:13,329
Disaster.

442
00:32:28,860 --> 00:32:31,756
Doctor, was there something else?

443
00:32:33,792 --> 00:32:34,992
No.

444
00:32:41,653 --> 00:32:43,177
I accepted it.

445
00:32:45,010 --> 00:32:47,487
I can do this. I can do this.

446
00:32:47,963 --> 00:32:51,043
I'm the Best of God Hand. I'm a genius.

447
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:56,316
I can do it. I can do it. I can do it.

448
00:32:58,762 --> 00:33:00,036
Doctor?

449
00:33:00,702 --> 00:33:03,709
I can do it! I can do it! I am...

450
00:33:05,762 --> 00:33:07,775
I'm the God Hand!

451
00:33:10,903 --> 00:33:12,255
Dr. Bonten!

452
00:33:13,183 --> 00:33:15,396
Hey, what happened?

453
00:33:21,070 --> 00:33:23,810
What's going on? How did this happen?

454
00:33:24,036 --> 00:33:25,910
Dr. Bonten, what's wrong?

455
00:33:26,050 --> 00:33:27,890
Shut up! I'm thinking!

456
00:33:27,930 --> 00:33:29,970
Dr. Bonten, are you alright?

457
00:33:30,276 --> 00:33:31,609
Dr. Bonten!

458
00:33:32,429 --> 00:33:34,416
- Dr. Bonten!
- Shut up.

459
00:33:36,010 --> 00:33:37,996
- Huh?
- Shut up! Shut up!

460
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:40,743
Shut up!

461
00:33:54,697 --> 00:33:57,137
Ashura? Why are you here?

462
00:33:58,216 --> 00:34:01,110
I'm taking over this battlefield.

463
00:34:01,136 --> 00:34:02,429
Don't be ridiculous!

464
00:34:02,485 --> 00:34:03,990
Don't barge in here!

465
00:34:04,030 --> 00:34:05,930
You're the one who started this.

466
00:34:08,210 --> 00:34:10,870
Patients clinging
to your reputation is only natural...

467
00:34:11,670 --> 00:34:14,830
But how dare you exploit them
for your own fame?

468
00:34:16,530 --> 00:34:17,810
You wouldn't understand.

469
00:34:18,350 --> 00:34:21,483
My father was president
of the Medical Association.

470
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:25,730
My brothers are a Diet member
and a medical professor at Touou Univresity.

471
00:34:26,336 --> 00:34:29,656
I crawled my way up
while enduring all that pressure.

472
00:34:30,410 --> 00:34:34,310
My entire life has been
a battlefield since birth.

473
00:34:34,690 --> 00:34:36,775
Every day is life or death!

474
00:34:36,815 --> 00:34:38,074
I don't get it at all.

475
00:34:39,663 --> 00:34:41,643
Risking your life just to protect yourself?

476
00:34:42,250 --> 00:34:43,811
All I care about is...

477
00:34:47,509 --> 00:34:49,516
the patient's life right in front of me.

478
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:55,536
- Starting the operation. Scalpel.
- Here.

479
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:00,743
- Electric scalpel.
- Here.

480
00:35:06,866 --> 00:35:08,409
- Sternal saw.
- Here.

481
00:35:13,863 --> 00:35:15,329
- Rib spreader.
- Got it.

482
00:35:19,930 --> 00:35:23,610
Has Dr. Anno ever performed
a cardiac tumor operation?

483
00:35:24,150 --> 00:35:28,930
Probably not. But Anno is
an emergency physician.

484
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:32,530
She'll do what's best for the patient.

485
00:35:33,496 --> 00:35:37,150
Damn it. Anno's the one operating?

486
00:35:42,510 --> 00:35:44,376
- Start cardioplegia.
- Got it.

487
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:51,106
Cardiac arrest confirmed.
Resecting the tumor.

488
00:35:51,146 --> 00:35:54,921
Are you crazy? It's huge.
It has even invaded the pulmonary artery.

489
00:35:54,961 --> 00:35:56,300
Removing all of it is impossible.

490
00:35:56,340 --> 00:35:58,186
- Forceps and Metzenbaum.
- Here.

491
00:36:06,620 --> 00:36:08,600
What if you can't reconstruct it?

492
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:13,713
Cardiac function is borderline,
but I’ll graft the resected pulmonary artery.

493
00:36:13,753 --> 00:36:15,786
- You help, too.
- Oh, okay.

494
00:36:17,660 --> 00:36:19,640
If you're interested, come over and watch.

495
00:36:20,042 --> 00:36:21,222
Are you mocking me?

496
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:23,166
You can take over if you can do it better.

497
00:36:24,213 --> 00:36:26,386
Typical for someone in the ER.

498
00:36:27,363 --> 00:36:30,384
You're so used to patients dying,
it doesn't scare you anymore.

499
00:36:31,075 --> 00:36:33,580
So you don't care
if it's a high-risk surgery.

500
00:36:33,620 --> 00:36:35,215
Of course it scares me.

501
00:36:39,682 --> 00:36:41,670
But I still have to do it.

502
00:36:43,995 --> 00:36:46,460
Living with regret
for not trying is far worse.

503
00:36:50,649 --> 00:36:51,874
Here you go.

504
00:36:53,390 --> 00:36:55,016
- Prolene suture 3-0.
- Here.

505
00:37:05,036 --> 00:37:06,269
So fast.

506
00:37:32,090 --> 00:37:33,583
- Mayo scissors.
- Here.

507
00:37:37,890 --> 00:37:41,063
- Suturing complete. Coming off bypass.
- Got it.

508
00:37:42,103 --> 00:37:45,109
- Releasing aortic cross-clamp. Flow down.
- Got it.

509
00:37:46,330 --> 00:37:47,890
- Back up.
- Yes.

510
00:37:48,310 --> 00:37:49,903
- Hot shot.
- Yes.

511
00:38:04,476 --> 00:38:06,800
Good, the heartbeat is back.

512
00:38:14,926 --> 00:38:16,162
V-fib?

513
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:18,160
Is there bleeding somewhere?

514
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:20,080
No, there's no bleeding.

515
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:23,680
Tumor fragments may be causing a blockage.
Get the defibrillator, now!

516
00:38:36,500 --> 00:38:41,720
Dr. Anno, let's check with an ultrasound.
The patient probably has...

517
00:38:46,020 --> 00:38:47,320
Atrial septal defect.

518
00:38:47,783 --> 00:38:48,783
You're right.

519
00:38:48,820 --> 00:38:51,560
But there were no symptoms
in the preoperative tests, right?

520
00:38:51,786 --> 00:38:55,305
He likely had a congenital hole
between the right and left atria.

521
00:38:55,345 --> 00:38:59,146
Not an issue in daily life, but coming off
the bypass was too much strain.

522
00:38:59,500 --> 00:39:02,753
The tumor hid the hole, so it wasn't visible
on the ultrasound before.

523
00:39:02,793 --> 00:39:06,799
We need closure surgery now.
We'll clamp the aorta.

524
00:39:06,839 --> 00:39:08,115
Wait.

525
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:13,140
You're scared, aren't you?

526
00:39:15,323 --> 00:39:16,686
I'll do the surgery.

527
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:20,716
- Flow down.
- Got it.

528
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:25,116
- Back up.
- Done.

529
00:39:27,363 --> 00:39:31,260
Hey, get me a new gown and gloves.

530
00:39:31,740 --> 00:39:33,823
- Understood.
- What are you doing?

531
00:39:39,046 --> 00:39:43,218
Dr. Anno, please return to your department.

532
00:39:47,241 --> 00:39:48,902
From now on,

533
00:39:50,341 --> 00:39:51,954
this is my battlefield.

534
00:40:02,330 --> 00:40:05,090
Then be my guest.

535
00:40:17,470 --> 00:40:21,030
We open the right atrium for patch closure.
Prepare the pericardial membrane.

536
00:40:30,950 --> 00:40:33,950
That's Ashura for you.

537
00:41:06,533 --> 00:41:07,896
You did a wonderful job.

538
00:41:08,475 --> 00:41:09,676
Thank you.

539
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:16,306
This is your fault.

540
00:41:18,420 --> 00:41:26,140
You may have considered me a friend,
but I never felt the same.

541
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:34,300
Since university, I could never forgive you
for always being ahead of me.

542
00:41:35,330 --> 00:41:37,676
No matter how hard I tried, I never won once.

543
00:41:40,733 --> 00:41:42,374
I was consumed by jealousy.

544
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:47,090
I never cared about climbing the ladder.

545
00:41:47,990 --> 00:41:55,810
I thought if I could drive you out
and win, I'd go from 99 percent to 100.

546
00:41:58,870 --> 00:42:02,880
But it seems I was wrong.

547
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:14,160
The one percent I was missing was the courage
to abandon self-preservation.

548
00:42:20,443 --> 00:42:22,450
Ashura made me realize that.

549
00:42:25,390 --> 00:42:27,430
Pass along my thanks.

550
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:42,470
Dr. Anno, great work on the surgery.

551
00:42:44,210 --> 00:42:47,050
Performing a cardiac tumor operation?
That's truly amazing.

552
00:42:47,810 --> 00:42:51,710
You're far more of a God Hand
than Dr. Bonten.

553
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:58,090
I almost died once.

554
00:43:02,583 --> 00:43:03,929
Dr. Anno?

555
00:43:05,349 --> 00:43:06,635
What?

556
00:43:07,037 --> 00:43:09,656
About what you said earlier...

557
00:43:12,057 --> 00:43:14,383
About nearly dying once.

558
00:43:33,288 --> 00:43:34,503
Incoming.

559
00:43:34,929 --> 00:43:36,129
Huh?

560
00:43:39,822 --> 00:43:41,029
Yes.

561
00:43:42,209 --> 00:43:43,589
Got it. Bring them in.

562
00:43:44,630 --> 00:43:45,917
Kid, let's go.

563
00:43:46,709 --> 00:43:48,022
Oh!

564
00:43:48,122 --> 00:43:49,323
Okay!

565
00:43:50,970 --> 00:43:53,490
What happened in Dr. Anno's past...

566
00:43:54,850 --> 00:43:58,483
In the end, I couldn't bring myself
to ask her that day.

567
00:43:59,636 --> 00:44:01,036
But that was exactly

568
00:44:02,350 --> 00:44:05,190
why Dr. Anno fought
on the battlefield of emergency medicine.

569
00:44:07,637 --> 00:44:09,357
That was her reason to fight.

570
00:44:09,863 --> 00:44:10,863
Next Episode Preview

571
00:44:10,890 --> 00:44:12,910
The ER will be shut down in two months.

572
00:44:13,130 --> 00:44:15,910
Dirty tactics or not, we have no choice.

573
00:44:15,950 --> 00:44:17,410
I'll take that fight.

574
00:44:17,477 --> 00:44:19,397
Why am I in the ER?

575
00:44:19,430 --> 00:44:21,110
I just wanna be useful.

576
00:44:21,150 --> 00:44:22,505
You call yourself a doctor?

577
00:44:22,545 --> 00:44:24,760
Anyone who plays
with lives has no place here.
